<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="352" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1657,2045]" pageId="6" pageNumber="352">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1657,1684]" pageId="6" pageNumber="352">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Pronotum subquadrate, many small denticles throughout the median carina of pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1289,1380,1658,1684]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lophotettix hancocki (Bruner, 1910) male holotype. (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/ Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491596/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="352">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
); anterior margin of median carina truncated and crest slightly arched, provide with two protuberances (
<figureCitation box="[1272,1363,1694,1720]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lophotettix hancocki (Bruner, 1910) male holotype. (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/ Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491596/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="352">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
); crest almost straight, with only one curve (
<figureCitation box="[570,657,1730,1756]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lophotettix hancocki (Bruner, 1910) male holotype. (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/ Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491596/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="352">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
, dorsal view); femora robust and with small lappets throughout on its dorsal margin (
<figureCitation box="[321,411,1766,1792]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lophotettix hancocki (Bruner, 1910) male holotype. (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/ Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491596/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="352">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="354" pageId="6" pageNumber="352" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1657,2045]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,153,935]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="354" pageId="6" pageNumber="352">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,656,1801,1828]" pageId="6" pageNumber="352">
Redescription (Male 
<typeStatus box="[452,556,1802,1828]" pageId="6" pageNumber="352">holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<figureCitation box="[570,641,1801,1828]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lophotettix hancocki (Bruner, 1910) male holotype. (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/ Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491596/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="352">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
):
</emphasis>
Body surface rugose and crest punctuated. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1153,1217,1802,1828]" pageId="6" pageNumber="352">Head</emphasis>
. Lateral view (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lophotettix hancocki (Bruner, 1910) male holotype. (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/ Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491596/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="352">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
): head and compound eyes inserted below median carina crest; protuberant and globose eyes with straight base; vertex and fastigium not visible between eyes; antennal groove situated below margin of compound eyes; facial carinae arched. Frontal view (
<figureCitation box="[486,576,1910,1936]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lophotettix hancocki (Bruner, 1910) male holotype. (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/ Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491596/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="352">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
): fastigium of vertex straight; eyes laterally arranged on the head but not pedunculated; frontal costa conspicuous, the bifurcation and facial carina visible; both superior ocelli between facial carinae; antennal grooves placed beside facial carinae; both antennae missing. Dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1208,1299,1982,2008]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lophotettix hancocki (Bruner, 1910) male holotype. (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/ Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491596/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="352">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
): vertex between eyes wider than eyes in horizontal and vertical diameter; supraocular lobe conspicuous; rectangularly shaped head. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[218,339,153,179]" pageId="8" pageNumber="354">Pronotum</emphasis>
. Macropronotal, rugose, subquadrate, erose, having irregular teeth and emarginations, many small denticles throughout the median carina of pronotum. Lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[898,989,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lophotettix hancocki (Bruner, 1910) male holotype. (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/ Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491596/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="354">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
): anterior margin of pronotum truncated and crest slightly arched, provided with two tubercle protuberances; median carina crest projection begins to decline after surpassing apex of tegmina and then becomes thinner; prozonal carina and extralateral carina inconspicuous; ventral sinus and tegminal sinus present; lateral lobe rounded and slightly directed laterally; infrascapular area narrow, thin and shorter than fore tibiae; wings slightly longer than pronotum. Frontal view (
<figureCitation box="[1159,1249,333,359]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lophotettix hancocki (Bruner, 1910) male holotype. (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/ Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491596/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="354">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
): lateral lobes of pronotum slightly projected and directed sideward. Dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[888,977,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lophotettix hancocki (Bruner, 1910) male holotype. (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/ Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491596/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="354">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
): median carina continuous and strongly elevated, straight, lateral lobes with rounded tip and small expansion. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[926,1105,404,431]" pageId="8" pageNumber="354">Sternomentum</emphasis>
. Inconspicuous. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1294,1370,404,431]" pageId="8" pageNumber="354">Wings</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lophotettix hancocki (Bruner, 1910) male holotype. (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/ Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491596/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="354">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
): tegmina and wings visible; wing longer than pronotum; tegmina ovoid and elongated, slightly thinner than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Lophotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alticristatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="354">L. alticristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1909" box="[341,503,478,503]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Lophotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unicristatus">
<emphasis box="[341,503,478,503]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="354">L. unicristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with rounded apex; tegmina without venation, but with small punctuations. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1373,1436,477,503]" pageId="8" pageNumber="354">Legs.</emphasis>
Fore legs (
<figureCitation box="[271,395,513,539]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lophotettix hancocki (Bruner, 1910) male holotype. (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/ Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491596/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="354">Fig. 4A, B</figureCitation>
): dorsal and ventral margins of femur with undulated carinae, right leg missing. Middle legs (
<figureCitation box="[159,237,549,575]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lophotettix hancocki (Bruner, 1910) male holotype. (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/ Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491596/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="354">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
A–B): dorsal and ventral margins of femur with undulated carinae with a dorso-apical blunt spine. Hind legs (
<figureCitation box="[160,284,585,611]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lophotettix hancocki (Bruner, 1910) male holotype. (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/ Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491596/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="354">Fig. 4A, B</figureCitation>
): femur robust and with small lappets throughout, on its dorsal margin. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1101,1225,584,611]" pageId="8" pageNumber="354">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Not visible on the type, completely covered by the pronotum (dorsal view) and hind femur (lateral view).
</paragraph>
